"Kim Jong Il Biography" Vol. 3 Off Press 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The International Institute of the Juche Idea in Japan published "Kim Jong Il Biography" Vol. 3 which deals with his outstanding personality as a great man and his immortal exploits.
 It introduces in detail his revolutionary activities in the period from January of Juche 79(1990) to February of Juche 91(2002). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed there are his portrait and a photo of him standing with President Kim Il Sung. It consists of 15 chapters (28-42). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chapters from 28 to 32 refer to the facts that in the first half of the 1990s he shattered the anti-socialist moves of the imperialists, firmly defended the socialist cause and further strengthened the People's Army, thus leading to a shining victory the struggle to smash the nuclear racket kicked up by the U.S. imperialists and defend the sovereignty of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chapters from 33 to 40 deal with the revolutionary activities he conducted under the uplifted banner of Songun in the period from July of Juche 83(1994) to the end of the 1990s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They recall the facts that he has significantly increased the defence capability through his ceaseless long journey for Songun leadership to cope with the U.S. imperialists' extremely undisguised moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK.
 Chapter 41 tells how he arranged the historic Pyongyang meeting which led to the adoption and publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and the opening of an epochal phase of national reunification and how he has developed the movement of Koreans in Japan onto a new higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chapter 42 deals with the facts that he made sure that the 55th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea was celebrated as a grand festival of victors of socialism and that he further augmented the might of the DPRK under the banner of Songun in the period from January of Juche 89(2000) to February of  Juche 91(2002).

Special Homepage Opens in Britain &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy opened Internet special homepage titled "74th Anniversary of Glorious Korean People's Army" on April 23 on the occasion of the 74th anniversary of the KPA.
 April 25 is a significant day when the KPA was founded, the homepage says, and goes on:
 The KPA founded by Generalissimo Kim Il Sung has grown to be a steel-like army under his wise guidance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA is a revolutionary army which defeated U.S. imperialism in the great Fatherland Liberation War and defended the socialist homeland of Juche as firm as a rock while shattering all the provocative moves of the enemy.
 Under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il the KPA has grown to be steel-like revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Supreme Commander of the KPA Kim Jong Il is a great strategist who is wisely leading the KPA, a-match-for-a hundred revolutionary armed forces, by carrying forward the revolutionary cause of Juche started by President Kim Il Sung.

Rodong Sinmun on Danger of U.S.-Japan Joint War Games 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The Asian people should pay attention to the ill-boding military moves of the U.S. and Japan and heighten vigilance against them, warns Rodong Sinmun in an article Friday. 
 Disclosing the serious danger of the U.S.-Japan joint war rehearsals staged in recent years in their scale, offensive nature and criminal purpose, the author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their dangerous nature lies in that they were all drills for the use of nuclear weapons and were targeted against the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are openly blustering that the Japan-U.S. joint military exercises are to cope with the "emergency on the Korean Peninsula."
 These exercises, without exception, have been conducted in areas close to the peninsula. The Japanese reactionaries have staged them with the U.S. navy by mobilizing the maritime "Self-defence Force" in the East Sea of Korea. This is a dangerous step in Japan's drive for a comeback to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Holding an ever bigger share in the U.S.-Japan joint military exercises are drills for coping with the "emergency on the Korean Peninsula".  The Japanese reactionaries set up a drill ground in Hokkaido which is similar to Korea in climatic and topographical conditions and let their ground SDF to stage joint war games frequently with U.S. troops. On the other hand, the SDF are intensifying mountain and nighttime warfare drills with the U.S. forces.  It is needless to say that they are, to all intents and purposes, a test war and a preliminary war to invade the DPRK.
 The danger of the exercises is all the greater because they followed hard on the heels of the U.S. publication of a "national security strategy report" in which it declared again the preemptive attack strategy as its national policy. In the joint military exercises against the DPRK, the U.S. and Japan have disclosed their sinister intention to mount a preemptive strike on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. seeks to provoke a new war on the Korean Peninsula and spread it to other regions while Japan intends to open up a wide avenue through the peninsula for the reinvasion of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Their outcries over "threat" from someone are sophism to justify their war moves.
 The reckless war moves of the U.S. imperialists and the Japanese reactionaries are rendering the situation on the Korean peninsula and its surroundings tenser and pose a grave threat to peace and security in Asia.

Powerful Spurs to Revolutionary Cause of Juche Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang-based papers Friday in editorials dedicated to the 70th anniversary of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland (ARF) call for dynamically advancing the revolutionary cause of Juche, guided by the idea of single-minded unity, which represents a symbol of Songun Korea and its dignity and future.
 The seven decades since the foundation of the ARF on May 5, Juche 25 (1936) represent a glorious history in which the single-minded unity of the Korean revolutionary ranks around the one central figure has been steadily cemented on the basis of the monolithic idea and a proud course in which they have brought about world-startling miracles and changes in the efforts to accomplish the socialist cause with the might of unity, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition of single-minded unity, the tradition of the great national unity provided in the crucible of the anti-Japanese war has been successfully carried forward by leader Kim Jong Il and its might has remarkably grown strong under his leadership.
 The leader, the Party, the army and the people in the DPRK are single-mindedly united to form a community linked with the same destiny. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole Party has been modeled on the Songun idea, the entire army shares the same idea, intention and destiny with the supreme commander and the army and the people achieved the perfect unity in idea and in the fighting traits on the basis of the spirit of devotedly defending the leader. This is the true picture of the single-minded unity in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition of unity established in the early period of the revolution has been confidently carried forward and has fully displayed its vitality generation after generation despite all sorts of ordeals and tests of history. This is the stirring reality that can be seen only in the DPRK led by the great leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK army and people will successfully accomplish the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation of Juche, singled-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il just as all the Korean people resolutely turned out in the anti-Japanese national united front movement to defeat the Japanese imperialist aggressors and achieve the historic cause of the country's liberation under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung. It is the oath taken by the DPRK army and people with faith on the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the ARF.
 It is a firm guarantee for the prosperity of the country and the victorious advance of the cause of Juche to firmly unite around Kim Jong Il. All the people should fully display the might of our single-minded unity in the general march of Songun revolution just as all the Koreans fought in close unity during the anti-Japanese war.
 Minju Joson calls for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche and the cause of national reunification as early as possible by successfully carrying forward the idea of the great national unity set out by the President and the exploits performed by him.

S. Korean Military Authorities' Move under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly issued a statement on April 29 denouncing the south Korean military authorities for their move to use forces for ensuring the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek. 
 The statement accused the Defence Ministry of contemplating the use of forces for forcibly evacuating inhabitants and facilities in the area of Phyongthaek after designating the area of Taechu-ri and Todu-ri of Phaengsong Town, Phyongthaek City of Kyonggi Province, as a "zone for the protection of military facilities."  The statement went on; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Defence Ministry let helicopters undergo a drill of landing on fields and conduct reconnaissance for choosing sites for posts and wire entanglements of the U.S. military base, etc., creating a terror-ridden atmosphere reminiscent of Kwangju drenched in blood in May of 1980. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Drawing attention to the fact that the ministry is set to crack down upon the fair-minded civilians desirous of tilling land in their hometown even by using forces for ensuring the expansion of the U.S. military base, the statement queries: Is there any difference from the monstrous massacre of Kwangju citizens committed by the fascist junta calling them "mobs"? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We cannot repress towering indignation at the ministry in its desperate bid to serve the interests of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hanchongryon will frustrate the ministry's plan to hurl forces into the area of Phyongthaek, braving any sacrifice and suppression, and use every possible means and method to deter GIs from intruding into even an inch of land there.

Fierce Struggle for U.S. Troops Pullout Vowed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 5 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils on April 28 reportedly issued a statement titled "Let's Force U.S. Troops Out of South Korea Inheriting Martyrs' Will." 
 The statement recalls that Ri Jae Ho, chairman of the Committee of Struggle for Peace against War and Nuclear Weapons of Seoul National University, and Kim Se Jin, chairman of the Student Council of the University of Natural Science, set themselves on fire on April 28, 1986 in protest against the U.S. imperialists bent on unleashing a nuclear war in Korea and the military fascist dictatorial "regime" forcing military education upon students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even though 20 years have passed since then, the statement says, the U.S. has not given up the nuclear war design but is putting spurs to war preparations for invading the north, involving the expansion of its military base in Phyongthaek for the purpose of "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. forces present in south Korea.  
 The atmosphere of national reunification produced by the publication of the June 15 joint declaration clearly proves that the north is not "our enemy" and there is no reason for the U.S. forces, the root cause of national division, to stay in south Korea any longer, notes the statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Calling for forcing the U.S. troops out of south Korea and bringing earlier the bright future of the Korean nation as laid down in the June 15 joint declaration, the landmark of national reunification, the statement underlines the need for the federation to stand at the head of the struggle against the U.S. and for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea, cherishing the anti-U.S. spirit of the martyrs.
